〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 . Ibid. but with all manner of Exhortations did entreat St. Mark, the Follower of St. Peter, that he would leave them in writing a digeſt or memorial of the Doctrine delivered to them by word of Mouth, and that they never ceaſed till they had obtained their requeſts; and that thus they were the cauſes of writing the Goſpel of St. Mark,

