verſe 14. or a brief Summary of the things which were to be believed by all; 〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉 , the good depoſitum, or Summary of Chriſtian Doctrine, committed to the truſt of others, or agreed on by the Apoſtles to be taught by all, 2 Tim. ij. 2. and which alſo was by them to be committed to faithful Men, able to inſtruct others in it:
